{{SupportPage|vendor=Belkin|vs_id=01t80000002wn1oAAA}} A triangular '''RoHS''' notice and "P/N: 141801620000J R01A" is silkscreened on one production model board. The default SSID pattern is '''belkin.XXX''' (and also [probably] '''belkin.XXX.5GHz''') where '''XXX''' is the last three hex digits of the wireless interface MAC address (lower case letters). An example SSID set is '''belkin.0a2''' and '''belkin.0a2.5GHz''' where the WLAN MAC is 08:86:3B:93:10:A2. {{WiFiCert|WFA11640|05/09/2011}} ==Serial== ===Boot log===
